        <item>
          <updateDate>2013-06-26T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Expresses the sense of the House of Representatives that allocating the appropriate resources to wildland fire management is needed to protect the environment, the economy, and the people of the United States.</p> <p>Urges the Forest Service to manage federal forest lands proactively in a manner that protects life and property, prevents catastrophic wildfire, promotes forest and watershed health, and creates jobs and economic development in the forest products industry.</p> <ul> <ul> </ul> </ul>]]></text>
